24/03/2023, 23:03 - IBC'22 Ashutosh Ojha: Greetings from Team IBC!

We are here for the interview process for the Model United Nations (MUN) Conference organised by Intellect Browsers' Consortium, the literary cum management society of MANIT. The first phase of the process starts on the 25th of March at 10:00 am.

These are your respective slots and timings for the interviews. Report at NTB 10 mins before your allotted time. In case of any prior engagement, the candidate can ask the panelists to reschedule the interview. 

We wish all the candidates an enriching experience and the best of luck!
See you on the other side!

#gnostos_perennia

20/08/2023, 11:06 - IBC'22 Twisha Nayak: Points to keep in mind for today:
20/08/2023, 11:07 - IBC'22 Twisha Nayak: 1. *Don't do ragging*.
2. First introduce yourself with your positions and then ask them to introduce themselves
3. Tell them about IBC.
4. Ask them to follow all the social media handles of IBC.
5. Guide them about being connected with full team.
6. Brief them about the events and ask them if they've any suggestions or improvements.
7. Tell them about the general rules and regulations of IBC which you all followed in your sophomore year.
8. Tell them to be attentive and be present in every meeting.
20/08/2023, 11:07 - IBC'22 Twisha Nayak: 9. Speak only in English. With them, amongst yourselves, even in the hostels if your juniors aproach you, speak in English.
10. Tell them about the minutes of the meeting, give them the sample format of the minutes of the meeting that we sent you and tell them one of them will have to make the proper minutes in every meeting.
20/08/2023, 11:07 - IBC'22 Twisha Nayak: 11. Start deciding the task that you'll need to give them. While making groups of any kind (for the task and for future events), make equal distribution genderwise. Try to put friends in separate group.
12. Tell them about your posts. What is it that you do, what is it that you are responsible for. Who do they need to approach of they have any issues. 
13. Before taking the first meet think of a small task that you want to allot to them, can be as trivial as Parv said, following IBC pages across social medias.
14. They are second years. Use the first meet to guide them about LinkedIn, ask them to make it, and increase their connections.
15. Gonna reiterate the English point once again. Its one thing IBC is known for, make sure everyone from both the years follows it. If someone is struggling, make them feel comfortable enough to try harder instead of being embarrassed.
16. Set the rules about deadlines very strictly. 
17. Let them know how to greet seniors, how to acknowledge messages. Why is it necessary etc
20/08/2023, 11:07 - IBC'22 Twisha Nayak: 18. Have your agenda clear before every meet (we used to make a list with points we wanna discuss, tasks we wanna allot). It'll help you ensure that time limit is never exceeded, and you'll be more efficient.
20/08/2023, 11:07 - IBC'22 Twisha Nayak: 19. Also if any friction occurs between them ask them to try to solve by themselves or ask to seniors to get it resolved.

08/12/2023, 17:59 - IBC'22 Smita Dharwa: Some points to remember while pitching of CAs-
1)The pitch should be done in English, only if they have difficulty understanding change the medium.
2)Introduce your college to them
3)Tell them about the IBC(Intellect Browsers Consortium) society, Literary cum Management society of NIT Bhopal, tell them what IBC does, mention about the literary and management events conducted by society like azure, MUN, Crescita, Market Guru,
4)Wrap up the above point s in 1 to 1.5 minutes
5)Tell them about Market Guru, give them little information about the actual event
6)Brag about the goodies we are providing, CA who brings 5 registrations will get free entry to the event, for 7 registrations they will get a certificate from NIT Bhopal, and for 10 or more registrations they will get Letter of Recommendation(LOR) from renowned professor of NIT Bhopal,tell them about advantages of LOR. Also brag about the registrations last year.
7)CA will have to post links and posters in their college groups for online promotion, if CA is convinced supply them the CA acceptance form and get the screenshot. If the person is not sure then call again.
8) If person doesn't accept the CA offer, ask for contact no. of CR or other friends, converting CR to CA has an advantage.
9)Also explain them what kind of promotion they need  to do like social media promotion and also getting the permission in their respective college if we visit their college.

22/12/2023, 18:45 - IBC'22 Smita Dharwa: Some points to remember while pitching of CAs-
1)The pitch should be done in English, only if they have difficulty understanding change the medium.
2)Introduce your college to them
3)Tell them about the IBC(Intellect Browsers Consortium) society, Literary cum Management society of NIT Bhopal, tell them what IBC does, mention about the literary and management events conducted by society like azure, MUN, Crescita, Market Guru,
4)Wrap up the above point s in 1 to 1.5 minutes
5)Tell them about Market Guru, give them little information about the actual event
6)Brag about the goodies we are providing, CA who brings 5 registrations will get free entry to the event, for 7 registrations they will get a certificate from NIT Bhopal, and for 10 or more registrations they will get Letter of Recommendation(LOR) from renowned professor of NIT Bhopal,tell them about advantages of LOR. Also brag about the registrations last year.
7)CA will have to post links and posters in their college groups for online promotion, if CA is convinced supply them the CA acceptance form and get the screenshot. If the person is not sure then call again.
8) If person doesn't accept the CA offer, ask for contact no. of CR or other friends, converting CR to CA has an advantage.
9)Also explain them what kind of promotion they need  to do like social media promotion and also getting the permission in their respective college if we visit their college.

24/01/2024, 13:33 - IBC'22 Rishikesh Kadam: Greetings from BITSMUN Goa!

We are excited to announce that we've returned with our *15th edition* scheduled to be held on the *16th-18th February, 2024.*

Join us to unravel your inner diplomat and get into heated debates with your peers, followed by lobbying in *The Socials, the formal delegate dinner at an exquisite location in Goa !*
With delegates coming from different parts of the world (Bangladesh, Istanbul, Dubai, Vietnam to name a few), enhance your MUN experience while competing for exciting delegate prizes!

Honored to announce that the esteemed *Kiran Bedi*, former Lieutenant Governor of Puducherry, will grace BITSMUN Goa '24 as the *chief guest*, adding invaluable insights to the diplomatic discourse.

Held parallel to *BITS Goa's annual technical fest, Quark '24*, don't miss the chance to attend the Quark's Aurora Nights, which have previously hosted *Amit Trivedi, Nikhil D'Souza, Sunidhi Chauhan, When Chai Met Toast, Darshan Rawal and popular comedians like Samay Raina.*

Here is a list of the tentative committees :-
1)DISEC
2)UNSC
3)Lok Sabha
4)Continuous Crisis Committee
5)ODC
6)Joint Crisis Committee
7)UNHRC
8)IP
9)EU

Visit us: https://linktr.ee/bitsmun

Form Link:
https://forms.gle/ox2ospbUGshCS5R66

Regards, 
Shubhay Gokhru 
Organising Committee 
BITSMUN Goa '24
